          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake the sponges, 16 to 18 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C fan. Line a 12-hole muffin tin with paper cases. Rub the {{lemon}} zest into the {{caster-sugar}} with your fingertips until the sugar smells strongly of lemon. Beat in the {{unsalted-butter}} until pale and fluffy. Add the {{eggs}} one at a time, beating after each. Fold in the {{plain-flour}} and {{baking-powder}}, then stir in the {{whole-milk}}. Divide evenly between the cases. Bake for 16 to 18 minutes until the sponges spring back when lightly pressed. Cool in the tin for 5 minutes, then transfer to a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the buttercream and ice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} until smooth and pale. Add the {{icing-sugar}} in two additions, beating well. Add the {{lemon-juice}} and beat for 3 minutes until the buttercream is fluffy and sharp. If it is too stiff, add a few drops more lemon juice. Pipe or spread onto the cooled cupcakes and scatter a little {{lemon}} zest over the top.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
